{
  "_comment": "Recorded input names for each pinned GitHub Action, from its action.yml at the pinned ref. tools/check-action-inputs.mjs verifies every `with:` key in .github/workflows/ is a real input here. GitHub SILENTLY IGNORES unknown `with:` keys, so a renamed input (e.g. first-interaction v3 moving to snake_case) kills a job with no error \u2014 this is the guard. When Dependabot bumps an action, this snapshot goes stale and the gate fails until a maintainer runs `node tools/dump-action-inputs.mjs --write`.",
